06/08/2009
MOSCOW, Russia -- President Dmitry Medvedev will visit Belgrade in October at the invitation of President Boris Tadic, the Kremlin announced on Wednesday (August 5th). Medvedev will take part in a Russian-Serbian "strategic partnership" summit. Talks will cover bilateral relations, but more importantly, joint energy projects Russia is promoting. Medvedev will also attend ceremonies marking the liberation of Belgrade in World War II. He will be the first Russian president to visit in years. (BBC - 06/08/09; Beta, B92, RTS, AFP - 05/08/09)
